reviews.text: I don't like coffee and Starbucks is the only place I can get a reliable cup of decent tea anywhere in the world and Hong King is no exception. Most coffee shops give you a cheap bag of Twinings or Lipton and charge you as much as an expensive cup of coffee. Not Starbucks.
Good place, quiter, cleaner but smaller then  ma on shan

As it is located near the entrace to the shopping mall, you can always smell the aroma coming from the coffee shop. However, the shop is often very stuffy when the sun sets. Also, the shop seems like it does not provide air conditioning, ventilation or circulation systems, which makes it really hard for people to enjoy coffee under the hot sun.

The location at middle to high class residential area are okay, but the temperature inside a glass enclosed green house are too high due to poor air circulation and radiation of sun light that needed to be improved.

Delicious coffee. I request soy milk instead of milk. Staff are very nice to help me. Vegetarian sandwiches are served. Small cafe with glasses. I enjoy the sunlight going in the cafe through the glasses roof and glasses window. A warm feeling during cold winter. The cafe is not busy. Baby chair is available.

reviews.text: Quiet place with some restaurants and a supermarket.  Locate near Lake Silver and Wu Kai Sha station.   Air is good and near sea.

Very quiet and pleasant environment. Uses natural lighting which feels quite nice. The modern design of the shopping mall plus the extraordinary WiFi makes it a great place. However, since it uses natural lighting, this place can get a bit stuffy on the top floor. There is not much variety of choices, as most shops are either restaurants or convenience
 stores.
All you would find here is restaurants after restaurants after restaurants. Plenty of food choices, but food quality's meh.
Nice, small and quiet shopping centre, not much to buy.  Clean and not many people, mainly residents.  Next to Lake Silver.  Lots of people bring their dogs around.  Lovely place
Romantic lighting at night. What a new era shopping mall for all age
